fips.counties

US county data

   1"""US county data"""
   2
   3from io import StringIO
   4
   5import pandas as pd
   6
   7class County:
   8    """Get county data
   9
  10    See `Counties()` for list of available county data. 
  11    """
  12    def __init__(self,**kwargs):
  13        """Construct a single county data object
  14
  15        # Arguments 
  16
  17        -  `**kwargs`: search criteria (e.g., `{ST="CA",COUNTY="Alameda"}`)
  18        """
  19        keys = list(kwargs.keys())
  20        values = list(kwargs.values())
  21
  22        try:
  23            self.data = Counties().set_index(keys).loc[[values]].reset_index()
  24        except KeyError:
  25            self.data = None
  26        if self.data is None or len(self.data) > 1:
  27            raise KeyError(f"{kwargs=} is not a valid unique key")
  28
  29    def __getattr__(self,key):
  30        return self.data[key].iloc[0]
  31
  32    def __str__(self):
  33        return f"{self.COUNTY} {self.ST} ({self.GEOHASH})"
  34
  35    def __repr__(self):
  36        return f"<County(FIPS={self.FIPS})>"
  37
  38    def to_dict(self):
  39        """Convert county data object to dict"""
  40        return {x:y[0] for x,y in self.data.to_dict('list').items()}
  41
  42class Counties(pd.DataFrame):
  43    """US counties dataframe
  44
  45    # Columns
  46
  47    - `ST`: state abbreviation
  48
  49    - `FIPS`: county FIPS code
  50
  51    - `COUNTY`: county/parish/burrough name
  52    
  53    - `LAT`: county centroid latitude
  54
  55    - `LON`: county centroid longitude
  56
  57    - `GEOHASH`: county centroid geohash
  58
  59    - `TZOFFSET`: state timezone offset
  60
  61    - `DST`: flag to indicate whether summer time is observed
  62
  63    - `SYSTEM`: system interconnection name
  64
  65    - `RO`: reliability organization name
  66
  67    # Caveat
  68
  69    - Some counties located along timezone boundaries may be split across two
  70      timezones. In such cases, the timezone selected covers the majority of
  71      the county's land area.
  72    """
  73    def __init__(self,
  74        state:str=None,
  75        use_index:str|list[str]=None
  76        ):
  77        """Construct a data frame of US counties
  78

  82
  83        - `use_index`: use the specified column(s) as the index

13    def __init__(self,**kwargs):
14        """Construct a single county data object
15
16        # Arguments 
17
18        -  `**kwargs`: search criteria (e.g., `{ST="CA",COUNTY="Alameda"}`)
19        """
20        keys = list(kwargs.keys())
21        values = list(kwargs.values())
22
23        try:
24            self.data = Counties().set_index(keys).loc[[values]].reset_index()
25        except KeyError:
26            self.data = None
27        if self.data is None or len(self.data) > 1:
28            raise KeyError(f"{kwargs=} is not a valid unique key")
29
30    def __getattr__(self,key):
31        return self.data[key].iloc[0]
32
33    def __str__(self):
34        return f"{self.COUNTY} {self.ST} ({self.GEOHASH})"
35
36    def __repr__(self):
37        return f"<County(FIPS={self.FIPS})>"
38
39    def to_dict(self):
40        """Convert county data object to dict"""
41        return {x:y[0] for x,y in self.data.to_dict('list').items()}

  43class Counties(pd.DataFrame):
  44    """US counties dataframe
  45
  46    # Columns
  47
  48    - `ST`: state abbreviation
  49
  50    - `FIPS`: county FIPS code
  51
  52    - `COUNTY`: county/parish/burrough name
  53    
  54    - `LAT`: county centroid latitude
  55
  56    - `LON`: county centroid longitude
  57
  58    - `GEOHASH`: county centroid geohash
  59
  60    - `TZOFFSET`: state timezone offset
  61
  62    - `DST`: flag to indicate whether summer time is observed
  63
  64    - `SYSTEM`: system interconnection name
  65
  66    - `RO`: reliability organization name
  67
  68    # Caveat
  69
  70    - Some counties located along timezone boundaries may be split across two
  71      timezones. In such cases, the timezone selected covers the majority of

US counties dataframe

Columns

  • ST: state abbreviation

  • FIPS: county FIPS code

  • COUNTY: county/parish/burrough name

  • LAT: county centroid latitude

  • LON: county centroid longitude

  • GEOHASH: county centroid geohash

  • TZOFFSET: state timezone offset

  • DST: flag to indicate whether summer time is observed

  • SYSTEM: system interconnection name

  • RO: reliability organization name

Caveat

  • Some counties located along timezone boundaries may be split across two timezones. In such cases, the timezone selected covers the majority of the county's land area.
